In statement released on Thursday, Prasa confirmed that Sithole tendered his resignation on 28 February and that the board has accepted it. JOHANNESBURG - The board of the Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa has accepted the resignation of interim CEO Sibusiso Sithole. In a statement released on Thursday, Prasa confirmed that Sithole tendered his resignation on 28 February and that the board has accepted it. Sithole was appointed on 1 June 2018 and had been at the helm for nine months. Dr Nkosinathi Sishi has been seconded to act as group CEO.